Ken Elkinson was born on August 28, 1972, in Cedar Grove, NJ. He studied classical piano at an early age, learning the instrument until he was 14, when he began to study jazz and pop styles. Elkinson picked up bass and guitar and studied music at Muhlenberg College in Allentown, PA.

Often more upbeat and joyful than Elkinson's 1996 debut album, "Midnight Conversation", "Revelry" introduces us to a maturing artist who has done a lot of growing in the past four years.This is a truly exceptional solo piano album, and one of my ten favorites for the year 2000.
